reviews.review_description:
I have been waiting for this game to come out for a month. It's peaceful to hunt for mushrooms and interact with non-violent animals. I can't wait to play it again today.

Update after two weeks of playing:

I have been exclusively playing this on my Quest 2 in the 15 days since I've bought it. It's pretty addictive. And peaceful.

THE GOOD

- The game keeps you hooked. I rarely get bored in it;
- Big levels. I wish there were more;
- High replayability;
- Peaceful environments to explore and plenty of stuff to gather. If you are tired of foraging you can always go metal detecting;
- I liked the easter eggs - they were funny;
- excellent price for such a good game;
- nice harvesting and gathering mechanics (you drop items over your body to collect);
- simple gameplay, fast learning curve;

THE BAD

- The music gets to you after a while. I keep hearing the same tracks and it's driving me insane. Caught myself humming the songs while I do the dishes or browse the web;
- Turning with the controller give you serious dizziness;
- Sometimes, when grabbing a seed and holding it in your hand, if you push forward you move backwards;
- When watering and fertilizing plants you have to hit the right spot to be able to view their stats;
- Opening doors takes a few tries when you aim for the door icon;
- Entering levels sometimes presents graphics without texture for about 5-10 seconds and after that the resolution is better;
- Going metal detecting quickly drains the controller's battery since it makes the controller vibrate constantly;
- When planting a seed, you need to keep it far away from your body, hand extended, otherwise it simply goes back in the inventory.

WHAT WOULD BE NICE TO HAVE

- more maps to buy at the market;
- a slightly bigger density of metal objects in the ground;
- better graphics wouldn't hurt;
- more audio tracks;
- more seeds to buy.


I can't wait for updates. Bought the game one minute after launch and it is by far one of the best I've played yet.
